ZH: 我不想过着碌碌无为的生活。
EN: I don't want to live a mediocre life.

ZH: 他整天碌碌无为，连个作品都没有。
EN: He does nothing all day, without a single piece of work to show for it.

ZH: 没有追求，我只会碌碌无为。
EN: Without ambition, I will just drift aimlessly.

ZH: 我不想一生碌碌无为，我要成就一番事业。
EN: I don't want to be mediocre my whole life, I want to achieve something great.

ZH: 再也躲不过这碌碌无为的命运。
EN: I can't escape this fate of being mediocre.

ZH: 只要肯付出努力，就不会碌碌无为。
EN: As long as you are willing to put in the effort, you won't be mediocre.

ZH: 他注定要过着碌碌无为的一生。
EN: He is destined to live a mediocre life.

ZH: 每个人都应该远离碌碌无为的状态。
EN: Everyone should stay away from mediocrity.

ZH: 这种碌碌无为的生活真是太无聊了。
EN: This kind of mediocre life is so boring.

ZH: 她不想要碌碌无为地过完一生。
EN: She doesn't want to live her whole life in mediocrity.

ZH: 每个人都有机会摆脱碌碌无为。
EN: Everyone has the chance to break free from mediocrity.

ZH: 没有人愿意过着碌碌无为的日子。
EN: No one wants to live a mediocre life.

ZH: 他渴望摆脱碌碌无为的生活。
EN: He longs to break free from mediocrity.

ZH: 我要证明自己不是碌碌无为的人。
EN: I want to prove that I am not a mediocre person.

ZH: 这种碌碌无为的生活令人沮丧。
EN: This mediocre life is depressing.

ZH: 不甘于碌碌无为，我会拼尽全力。
EN: I refuse to be mediocre and will give it my all.

ZH: 他的碌碌无为已经持续了好几年。
EN: His mediocrity has lasted for several years.

ZH: 坚持努力，不要沉沦于碌碌无为。
EN: Keep working hard and don't sink into mediocrity.

ZH: 她害怕自己会碌碌无为地度过一生。
EN: She is afraid of living a mediocre life.

ZH: 我不想沦为碌碌无为的代表。
EN: I don't want to be the epitome of mediocrity.
